<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="_-OtaYN0MEdmhp5PapAYf4w" name="refine_system_structure,{43DD441B-6B4C-4998-B5D9-2A15894C5D56}" guid="_-OtaYN0MEdmhp5PapAYf4w" changeDate="2005-11-14T13:46:52.830-0800" version="7.1.0">
  <sections xmi:id="_AaA0UN0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w" name=" Review changes " guid="_AaA0UN0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Review Changes&quot; name=&quot;Review Changes&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The System Architect is prompted to perform this activity by:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        any significant change in the system's environment (reflected in the &lt;i>system context,&lt;/i> the top-level&#xD;
        collaboration between the system and its actors)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        refactoring during &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/se_operation_design_FE6558AC.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_Gb4P8OQ7Edm1mN374l9mbg&quot;>Task: System Operation Design&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        feedback on &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_vision_AE7C87FE.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{892CEA8C-66C5-468C-8188-F739B3954B90}&quot;>Artifact: Subsystem Vision&lt;/a> or &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_supplementary_specification_911D5D8E.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{C9B8F699-A008-4A3E-8B4D-CE829D595E5D}&quot;>Subsystem Supplementary Requirements&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        the System Architect's own refinements made in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/refine_system_deployment_model_AAD44C73.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{B8F36D9E-D010-4D38-8E2F-57B28CC16D1A}&quot;>Task: Refine System Deployment Model&lt;/a> and &lt;a&#xD;
        class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/refine_system_processes_3AFDF977.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{6A132C87-C82B-422D-BD56-B42E7E20131D}&quot;>Task: Refine System Processes&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The System Architect examines these changes to determine what effect, if any, they have on the logical viewpoint, that&#xD;
    is, the way the system is decomposed into collaborating subsystems.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_AaG68N0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w" name=" Refactor/augment subsystems " guid="_AaG68N0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Refactor/Augment Subsystems&quot; name=&quot;Refactor/Augment Subsystems&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The System Architect determines the subsystem structure initially in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/architectural_analysis_30D2538.html&quot; guid=&quot;{B7FABC7A-42FA-4DC7-A1F4-C4F5DB6F673F}&quot;>Task:&#xD;
    System Architectural Analysis&lt;/a>, then the detail of how subsystems collaborate is added by the System Designer in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/se_operation_analysis_6C6BED14.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_GMjFYOQ5Edm1mN374l9mbg&quot;>Task: System Operation Analysis&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;and then&amp;nbsp; &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/se_operation_design_FE6558AC.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Gb4P8OQ7Edm1mN374l9mbg&quot;>Task: System Operation&#xD;
    Design&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;perhaps doing some refactoring in the process. In the light of this work and any other changes or&#xD;
    feedback, the System Architect examines the System Use-Case Realizations (subsystem interactions) to check the validity&#xD;
    of the subsystem model, and then adjusts it if necessary.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_AaNBkN0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w" name=" Capture updated Logical viewpoint in System Architecture Document " guid="_AaNBkN0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Capture Updated Logical Viewpoint in System Architecture Document&quot;&#xD;
name=&quot;Capture Updated Logical Viewpoint in System Architecture Document&quot;>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Decisions made in this activity are captured in the System Analysis Model (if this is separately maintained) and System&#xD;
    Design Model; those aspects which the System Architect considers to be significant are also recorded in the &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_system_architecture_document_C5DEEFE5.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{F411BB0B-C101-4D78-96B9-10749A72EAD8}&quot;>Artifact: System Architecture Document&lt;/a> (in this case as part of the&#xD;
    &lt;i>Logical&lt;/i> viewpoint).&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_AaNBkd0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w" name=" Update subsystem requirements artifacts " guid="_AaNBkd0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Update Subsystem Requirements Artifacts&quot; name=&quot;Update Subsystem Requirements Artifacts&quot;>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If changes are made to the partitioning, then the corresponding requirements artifacts, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_vision_AE7C87FE.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{892CEA8C-66C5-468C-8188-F739B3954B90}&quot;>Subsystem Vision&lt;/a>, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_supplementary_specification_911D5D8E.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{C9B8F699-A008-4A3E-8B4D-CE829D595E5D}&quot;>Subsystem Supplementary Requirements&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_usecase_model_9C336055.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{124F1EA8-21EC-45C2-A25B-A8DCF1309FE4}&quot;>Subsystem Use-Case Model&lt;/a>, might also have to be updated.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_AaNBkt0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w" name=" Evaluate the results " guid="_AaNBkt0NEdmhp5PapAYf4w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Evaluate the Results&quot; name=&quot;Evaluate the Results&quot;>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The effectiveness of proposed solutions at all levels need to be reviewed with the stakeholders and the development&#xD;
    team to ensure that all requirements (cost, capability, constraints) are satisfied, and that the rationale (domain&#xD;
    conventions, architectural considerations of cohesion and coupling, and so on) for arriving at the particular&#xD;
    decomposition is sound. The chosen decomposition must also satisfy any political or economic mandate for subcontracted&#xD;
    development of subsystems. Techniques such as simulation and prototyping can be used to provide more objective&#xD;
    demonstrations of the adequacy of the design(s).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>Based on work done on subsystem interactions, Subsystem Supplementary Requirements, Subsystem Vision, and changes in the&#xD;
environment, to refine the System Analysis and System Design Models (in terms of subsystems and their relationships) and&#xD;
update the Subsystem Vision.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
